4
5 SECTION 2. EMERGENCY CLAUSE. It is found and determined by the
6 General Assembly of the State of Arkansas that the operations of a state
7 public retirement system are complex; that the Arkansas Teacher Retirement
8 System must be able to meet the needs of its members as anticipated by the
9 General Assembly; that certain provisions of the Arkansas Teacher Retirement
10 System Act, ยง 24-7-201 et seq., need immediate revision and updating to
11 address administrative complexities caused by these provisions and to bring
12 these provisions into conformance with sound public pension policy and
13 actuarial requirements; that the revisions and updates are of great
14 importance to members of the Arkansas Teacher Retirement System and to other
15 citizens of the State of Arkansas; that as the Arkansas Teacher Retirement
16 System operates on a fiscal year of July 1 to June 30, an effective date of
17 July 1, 2025, is necessary in order to allow the provisions within this act
18 to begin on the first day of the fiscal year and to allow for a structured
19 and proper administration of the procedures referenced in this act; that the
20 updates and revisions to the Arkansas Teacher Retirement System Act are of
21 great importance and necessary for protecting member benefits and clarifying
22 the reporting and contribution requirements of employers participating in the
23 Arkansas Teacher Retirement System; and that this act is necessary in order
24 to maintain an orderly system of benefits for the members of the Arkansas
25 Teacher Retirement System. Therefore, an emergency is declared to exist, and
26 this act being necessary for the preservation of the public peace, health,
27 and safety, shall become effective on July 1, 2025.
